Health officials in Hong Kong are investigating a deadly strain of bird flu that has caused global concern.
The virus, H5N1, has claimed lives, sparking a hunt for its source.
Experts are considering the development of a vaccine while urging caution but not panic among residents.
Measures include increased monitoring of chicken diseases and advice to buy poultry only from licensed vendors.
Despite suspected cases, there is no evidence of human-to-human transmission.
Tourists are reassured that the risk is low, and strict preventive measures in neighboring areas have kept the virus at bay.
